<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Slender1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Slender,</orth> 1) thin, slim, not thick or gross: <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.112" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.256" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 256</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.162" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 162</bibl> <cit><quote>(--er).</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 3.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 2, 61</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) small, inconsiderable, insufficient: <cit><quote>of s. reputation,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 3, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>s. wit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 49</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>at so s. warning,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 4, 60</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a thin and s. pittance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 4, 60</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>means,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.159" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 159</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>some s. ort of his remainder,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.400" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 400</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>on s. accident,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 209</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>